| Error Type              | How to Debug / Fix                                                 |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| CSV parsing issues      | Check header names, use `try-except` around float conversion.      |
| File not found          | Confirm `data/report.csv` exists, use `os.path.exists()` to check. |
| ValueError (float fail) | Print row contents before converting to `float`.                   |
| Unit mismatches         | Add logging to track marker names and units.                       |
| Missing reference range | Print warnings for unknown markers.                                |
g++ -std=c++17 -g -o health_analyzer main.cpp
gdb ./health_analyzer
Handle Security Concerns
Disallow arbitrary file uploads.

Run on a secure server.

Validate all filenames and limit extensions (.csv, .pdf).

Sanitize output shown in web interface (FastAPI: use Pydantic schemas).

Keep dependencies up to date (pip install --upgrade or apt/brew).

